<h2>Lodging steps</h2>
<ol>
  <li>Print the Simple Procedure claim form on white A4. Do not alter the form layout.</li>
  <li>Attach the particulars, arrears schedule, interest sheet and evidence index to the form.</li>
  <li>Gather supporting evidence (tenancy agreement, rent payment records, photos, invoices) following the index order.</li>
  <li>Lodge the bundle at the Sheriff Court along with the correct court fee.</li>
  <li>The court will serve the claim on the defender and set a hearing date.</li>
</ol>

<h2>Simple Procedure notes</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Claims must be under £5,000 (claim value excluding interest and expenses)</li>
  <li>Court fees range from £21 to £145 depending on claim value</li>
  <li>You must show attempts to resolve the dispute before raising a claim</li>
  <li>The sheriff will manage the case informally - this is designed to be accessible without a solicitor</li>
</ul>

